## Module System & Import Patterns

**ES Modules (Native):**
- All modules use ES6 `import`/`export` syntax
- Import paths are relative: `'./modules/core/constants.js'`
- Always include `.js` extension in imports
- No CommonJS (`require`) in source code

**Module Categories:**
- `core/` - State, constants, lifecycle
- `physics/` - Physics engine, collisions, spawning
- `rendering/` - Canvas, rendering loop, visual effects
- `modes/` - Simulation mode implementations
- `ui/` - User interface, panels, controls, gates
- `input/` - Mouse/touch input handling
- `audio/` - Sound system
- `visual/` - Colors, themes, visual effects
- `utils/` - Utility functions
- `portfolio/` - Portfolio-specific code

**Import Pattern Examples:**
```javascript
// Named exports (preferred)
import { CONSTANTS } from './modules/core/constants.js';
import { initState, getGlobals } from './modules/core/state.js';

// Default exports (when appropriate)
import Ball from './modules/physics/Ball.js';

// Side-effect imports (for initialization)
import './modules/ui/panel-dock.js';
```

**File Naming:**
- Modules: `kebab-case.js` (e.g., `mode-controller.js`, `dark-mode-v2.js`)
- Classes: `PascalCase.js` (e.g., `Ball.js`)
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` in code
- Functions: `camelCase`

